<title>USA: AlliedSignal says to acquire Prestone.</title>
<headline>AlliedSignal says to acquire Prestone.</headline>
<dateline>MORRIS TOWNSHIP, N.J. 1997-05-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>AlliedSignal Inc said on Monday that it had agreed to buy Prestone Products Corp, a privately owned supplier of car care products with annual sales of about $300 million.</p>
<p>AlliedSignal did not disclose a purchase price, but said it expected the transaction to close in June.</p>
<p>Allied also said it had agreed to buy Prestone from Prestone management and from Vestar Capital Partners, a private investment firm and the controling shareholder of Prestone.</p>
